<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-05-26T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-05-26T02:00:00-05:00" n="475" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">195.2/2701: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul in Chargé at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Price</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shameen</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-05-26T15:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">May 26,
                                        1921—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received May 27—1:16
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>American companies operating under charter Chinese-owned vessels plying
                            inland waters desire to fly the flag of the United States at the
                            masthead to indicate charter interests, the vessels continuing <pb facs="0648" n="524" xml:id="pg_524"/> fly the flag of China aft and
                            remain operating Chinese registry, Chinese authorities acquiescing and
                            other nationals permitted. Does the Department sanction or prohibit?
                            Please reply by telegraph as early as possible.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>